{"id":"octal-to-decimal","slug":"octal-to-decimal","name":"Octal to Decimal Converter","category":"converters","icon":"💻","description":"Convert octal (base-8) numbers to decimal. Each octal digit represents a power of 8.","tags":["octal","decimal","base-8","number system","converter"],"fields":[{"id":"octalInput","label":"Octal digits (ones position value, 0-7)","type":"number","defaultValue":7,"constraint":{"min":0,"max":7,"step":1}},{"id":"tensOctal","label":"Tens octal digit (0-7)","type":"number","defaultValue":1,"constraint":{"min":0,"max":7,"step":1}},{"id":"decimal","label":"Decimal value","type":"computed","precision":0,"helpText":"tensOctal × 8 + onesOctal"},{"id":"hex","label":"Hex value (0-F range)","type":"computed","precision":0},{"id":"binary","label":"Needs N bits","type":"computed","precision":0}],"groups":[{"id":"inputs","label":"Octal Digits","fields":["tensOctal","octalInput"]},{"id":"outputs","label":"Decimal","fields":["decimal","hex","binary"]}],"formulas":{"decimal":"tensOctal * 8 + octalInput","hex":"tensOctal * 8 + octalInput","binary":"ceil(log(tensOctal * 8 + octalInput + 1, 2))"},"explanation":"## Octal to Decimal\n\nMultiply each digit by its power of 8:\n\n**Example:** 17₈ = 1×8 + 7 = **15**\n\n**Example:** 100₈ = 1×64 = **64**","examples":[{"label":"17 octal → 15","inputs":{"tensOctal":1,"octalInput":7}},{"label":"77 octal → 63","inputs":{"tensOctal":7,"octalInput":7}}]}
